<bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
<head>Historical and Biographical Information</head>
<p>Wayne Hill, a local photographer, collected stereoviews over a period of years. Born in Washington D.C., Hill attended Dartmouth College and graduated in 1966 with a B.A. in Environmental Psychology. After working with noted photographic artist Ansel Adams in California, Hill started his own company in Virginia called The HILL Art Group. For fifty years, Hill’s company has focused on photographing American National Parks and other scenic locations around the globe. In addition to his many artistic accomplishments and awards, Hill is the former President and CEO of Leadership Fairfax, Inc. and a former Board Member of the Fairfax County Chamber of Commerce and Greater Reston Chamber of Commerce.</p>
</bioghist>




